stylometry: Aggregate planning is when you are planning something that is going to be using numbers and formulas to solve this problem or plan.  This allows you to come up with a solution that will answer is you plan going to be a success or not.  You need to consider that in aggregate planning there is going to be some error with the computer and you may have to change the starting point.  Some of the tradeoffs are that you may not be getting a wide enough range though what you are trying to plan.  We did an example with cities and who is living there and you may not be getting enough information to allow you to make the correct business decision.
